text:
as a california business, i hope you are on top of your sexual harassment prevention training requirements for all your managers. however, this year california expanded training requirements to your non-supervisory employees as well. new senate bill 1343 ("sb 1343") also extends training requirements to all the companies with five or more employees. 
sb 1343 requires covered employers to provide at least two hours of sexual harassment prevention training to all supervisory employees and at least one hour of  training to all non-supervisory employees by january 1, 2020. training and education must be provided once every two years after that, as specified under the new law.
also, employers must provide sexual harassment prevention training to temporary or seasonal employees within 30 calendar days after the hire date or within 100 hours worked if the employee will work for less than six months. in the case of a temporary employee employed by a temporary services employer (as defined by the california labor code) to perform services for clients, the training must be provided by the temporary services employer, not the client. the anti-sexual harassment training may be conducted with other employees, as a group, or individually, and broken up into shorter time segments, as long as the two-hour requirement for supervisory employees and the one-hour requirement for non-supervisory employees is reached.
 #sb1343 #metoo #hr #sexualharassment #training #california #employees #entreprenuer #business #doingbusinessinca #eastwestgeneralcounsel

text:
after serving 15 years in prison, cyntoia brown will be released on aug. 7 and will remain on parole for 10 years. brown, an alleged sex trafficking victim serving a life sentence for the 2004 murder of a man who picked her up and took her to his home, was 16 years old when she committed the crime in what she described as an act of self-defense.
â€¢
brownâ€™s story spread widely in the fall of 2017 amid the #metoo movement. supporters rallied around her case with the hashtag #freecyntoiabrown, calling it an example of the countryâ€™s unjust incarceration of children and victims of sex trafficking. kim kardashian highlighted the case to president trump in a meeting last may over prison reform. â€œi am thankful for all the support, prayers, and encouragement i have received,â€ brown said. â€œwe truly serve a god of second chances and new beginnings.â€
â€¢
while in prison, brown has earned her ged and an associate degree with a 4.0 gpa, according to a statement from tennessee gov. bill haslam. she has one course left to complete her bachelorâ€™s degree, which she expects to finish in may of this year. â€œwith godâ€™s help, i am committed to live the rest of my life helping others, especially young people,â€ brown said. â€œmy hope is to help other young girls avoid ending up where i have been.â€ (photo by lacy atkins/tennessean/ap; illustration by @thelilynews)

text:
i don't watch a lot of news so i just found out about surviving r. kelly. if you know me, you know that when i am interested in a case i bury myself in it. we need to stop supporting people who abuse children. i don't care how good their musical talent is, nothing makes it ok. the fact that r. kelly used his fame and power to do this makes it all even worse. the fact that his album sales have increased since the docuseries, makes me even more infuriated that there are more people wanting to support this monster.

photo description: jessica is wearing a purple off the shoulder t-shirt. she is holding her hand up with the word stop written on it. she is looking into the camera lens but is not smiling.

text:
itâ€™s finally time to bring â€˜beneath the veilâ€™ into the world ğŸŒ¹

you can pre-order your copy now and be holding her in your hands in two weeks! âœ¨

www.bernadetteoconnor.com/sales (linkinbio)

beneath the veil is the spellbinding new novel from bestselling author, bernadette oâ€™connor, recounting the story of clara, and her quest for truth, freedom and wisdom. â€˜many a time, she left me completely bewildered and i learnt to embrace the mystery of not knowingâ€”letting go of the need to knowâ€”allowing myself to feel my way through life once again,â€™ clara said to maeve. this is the story of clara, a beautiful young irish girl, and her quest for what lies beneath the veil. 
they see in her a gift but must let her make her own voyage of discovery. as clara seeks her freedom, she struggles to find the divine light to transform herself. haunted by the dark secrets of her past: a deadly betrayal, unspoken and unspeakable, she is too scared to reveal her truth, knowing she will be further condemned and punished by her brother or father colin stanley or padraig mcdermott. 
her silence a betrayal of her soul. she waits in the nothingness, scared, she too, will become a fallen woman of the magdalene laundry. locked away. as she listens through the silence that surrounds her, the blood-stained truth engulfs her and her family. she must symbolically cleanse herself of her sins while the endless penance to god continues through abuse, humiliation and beatings. 
on her journey she is reunited with her aunt maeve, a wise woman who teaches her the gypsy ways and how to dance with the truths of the world. guided by maeve, clara begins a spiritual odyssey into realms of light and shadow, toward a final communion that will awaken or destroy her. will she rise from the darkness of the past and be free from the indoctrination of the remote irish catholic village? 
this tale, told with heart, speaks to the soul in each of us, delivering moments of illumination, a potent mix of divine feminine and masculine history, which will inspire you to remember who you are. ultimately, beneath the veil is a story about being able to forgive our past and trust in our becoming.

on her journey she is reunited with her aunt maeve, a wise woman who teaches her the gypsy ways and how to dance with the truths of the world. guided by maeve, clara begins a spiritual odyssey into realms of light and shadow, toward a final communion that will awaken or destroy her. will she rise from the darkness of the past and be free from the indoctrination of the remote irish catholic village? 
this tale, told with heart, speaks to the soul in each of us, delivering moments of illumination, a potent mix of divine feminine and masculine history, which will inspire you to remember who you are. ultimately, beneath the veil is a story about being able to forgive our past and trust in our becoming.

text:
(cnn) cyntoia denise brown, a woman serving a life sentence for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16 years old, has been granted clemency, the tennessee governor's office said monday.

brown, 30, will be released to parole supervision on august 7 after serving 15 years in prison, gov. bill haslam's office said in a statement. "this decision comes after careful consideration of what is a tragic and complex case," haslam said.

#cyntoiabrown committed, by her own admission, a horrific crime at the age of 16. yet, imposing a life sentence on a juvenile that would require her to serve at least 51 years before even being eligible for parole consideration is too harsh, especially in light of the extraordinary steps ms. brown has taken to rebuild her life. transformation should be accompanied by hope." brown's case drew the attention of several high-profile advocates including a us congressman, several tennessee lawmakers and a number of a-list celebrities. comedian amy schumer, reality star #kimkardashianwest, #rihanna and actress #ashleyjudd were among those who called for brown's clemency.

text:
this is why we must continue to fight for justice. cyntoia brown, a victim of child sex trafficking and rape, was granted clemency by tennessee governor, bill haslam. brown was previously sentenced to life in prison for shooting and killing 43-year-old armed child predator johnny allen, who bought cyntonia for sex when she was just 16 years old.

at the time cyntoia was living with a 24-year old pimp who went by the name "kut throat," who forced her into prostitution and raped her repeatedly. "the first time he did something to me is when he choked me and i passed out," brown recounts of her alleged pimp in the documentary. "i made him money...he wasn't going to let me go nowhere. he told me he'd kill me." cyntoia said she was scared for her life by allen's behavior, and took money after killing him for fear of returning empty handed to her pimp. despite clearly being the victim of child sex trafficking, cyntoia was tried as an adult and convicted of murder and robbery, and sentenced to life in prison.

if you look at cyntoia's original transcripts, they are peppered with the phrase "teen prostitute." but there is no such thing as a teen prostitute. a teen is a trafficking victim being manipulated and exploited by an adult.

despite national protest, in december,Â tennesseeâ€™s supreme court ruled that cyntoia must remain in prison for at least 51 years before she was eligible for release.Â a lawsuit was filed on her behalf arguing that mandatory life sentences without parole for juveniles was unconstitutional. the court rejected that contention, leading the womenâ€™s march to announce nationwide protests for brown and other sex-trafficking victims on jan. 19.
our voices have been heard. 
a survivor will be set free this year.

text:
(cnn) cyntoia denise brown, a woman serving a life sentence for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16 years old, has been granted clemency, the tennessee governor's office said monday.

brown, 30, will be released to parole supervision on august 7 after serving 15 years in prison, gov. bill haslam's office said in a statement. "this decision comes after careful consideration of what is a tragic and complex case," haslam said.

#cyntoiabrown committed, by her own admission, a horrific crime at the age of 16. yet, imposing a life sentence on a juvenile that would require her to serve at least 51 years before even being eligible for parole consideration is too harsh, especially in light of the extraordinary steps ms. brown has taken to rebuild her life. transformation should be accompanied by hope." brown's case drew the attention of several high-profile advocates including a us congressman, several tennessee lawmakers and a number of a-list celebrities. comedian amy schumer, reality star #kimkardashianwest, #rihanna and actress #ashleyjudd were among those who called for brown's clemency.
#metoo#muterkelly #survivor#wosdvamwalk2019 #wosest2014 #velvetglovemedia #ce2

text:
i finished two books last night and somehow all of the three books i have read this year have sexual assault as a main theme. 
and my first book that was entirely queer centric hysterical, was a difficult read for that reason. as much as i love gathering the stories of other queer people to hold in my heart, it gets exhausting to not only read about all of these traumatic things, but then later have to translate and condense all of that knowledge into an all too short 1000 word article.

it can feel like a betrayal to the memory of the people i write about to leave something out, but the cutting room floor is always full, and i just hope i have made the right choices. no matter what though, each story leaves me with something, a glimmer of hope, a fun story to share, a new admiration or hatred for a person. but i have a feeling this one will leave me with a small tear. 
so while i am happy to learn i am also hoping the next book i pick up will be more healing.
#metoo #queerbooks #queerauthor #queerepresentation #queerwriting #queernovel #queerwriter #queerwriters #annafrued #lesbian #booksofinstagram #bookish #bookstagram #readersofinstagram #readergram

text:
to say that i am disgusted after watching â€˜surviving r. kellyâ€™ is an understatement and if the myriad of disturbing comments in the comments section of any article about the lifetime documentary series are any indication as to the mental and emotional state of the black community at large, r. kelly may never face justice, at least not by the u.s. justice system.

though not confined to the same prison as r. kellyâ€™s victims and survivors, many black men and women are just as brainwashed by his manipulative mania let alone distracted by his musical talent. after sitting through and watching almost six hours of interviews, if we were to replay his music (i donâ€™t recommend it) and listen intently with discerning ears, weâ€™d all realize that we have been listening to explicit stories of sexual abuse and aggression all along.

yet, today in 2019, in response to the eyewitness stories of sexually abused black girls and black women in high definition, other black girls, black men, and black women say, â€œit doesnâ€™t add upâ€. to whom i ask, what is there to add up? did we watch the same episodes? the research has already been done for us.

still, others have said â€œwho am i to judge?â€, which, to me, is a complete copout. the entire conversation from #blacklivesmatter to #metoo to #muterkelly is not about judging anyone but raising the level of national consciousness and holding perpetrators of crimes accountable for their actions.

as a black man, i am appalled that any man could defend or support the actions of r. kelly whether directly or indirectly. the adult complicity in this entire sex cult spans decades. truth be told, we all need healing because many of us have never learned what love is and what love is not, and to that end, we do not love ourselves.

i truly hope that at least one person that was asleep before is now awake. iâ€™ve muted r. kelly years ago and will continue to do so.

#muterkelly #metoo #blacklivesmatter #blackgirlsmatter #blackwomenmatter #blackwriters #blackbloggers #blackmen #blackwomen #blackpeople #blackculture #blackchurches #blackcommunity #seesomethingsaysomething #endsexualviolence #endsextrafficking #letthehealingbegin #arebelwithapen

in light of the docuseries #survivingrkelly, let this help us understand how certain behaviors perpetuates the destructive culture we have today that some people still defend. we will not stop educating everyone.
.
.

these behaviors are not a simple joke, a simple touch, harmless banter or any other unfrevilous excuse we can/have come up with. nip them in the bud, first expression of such should be immediately corrected.

text:
bohemian rhapsody won two â€œunexpectedâ€ awards at the golden globes, including best actor for rami malek and best motion picture (drama), catapulting the film into a legitimate oscars front-runner.
.
that â€œwhooooooshâ€ noise you just heard was a can of gasoline being emptied onto the now-raging inferno that is the academy awards. it all leads to the question: are you ready for the most problematic oscars ever?
.
the film itself is a wash, a pandering and disrespectful portrait of a complicated man and artist that all but erases his queerness for the sake of placating four-quadrant crowds. but plenty of bad movies have won golden globes, and oscars, too. what is more troubling is the fact that the film arrived in todayâ€™s #metoo and #timesup climate â€“ an era when power players and gatekeepers across the industry have pledged real change â€“ courtesy (sort of) director bryan singer.
.
in december of 2017, singer was accused of sexual assault by cesar sanchez-guzman, citing an alleged 2003 incident when sanchez-guzman was 17. in 2014, former child actor michael egan claimed in a lawsuit that the director sexually assaulted him in 1999. egan later withdrew his suit, and singer has denied all the accusations.
.
a few days before sanchez-guzman filed a lawsuit against singer, the director was fired from bohemian rhapsody by 20th century fox, with the studio citing the â€œunexpected unavailabilityâ€ of the filmmaker during production.
.
fox hired director dexter fletcher to complete filming, but singer retained his directing credit â€“ even if his name was not uttered once at the golden globes. when asked backstage about singer, who did not attend sunday nightâ€™s gala, bohemian rhapsody producer graham king said, â€œthatâ€™s not something we should talk about tonight.â€
.
so if not sunday night, then when? on the eve of the academy awards, perhaps, now that bohemian rhapsody is all but guaranteed a best-picture nomination? the answer, more likely, is never â€“ especially if weâ€™re trusting the academy awards to stand up where the golden globes fell down.
â€”

text: over the last several days, many individuals have learned about the horrific acts of violence and abuse that myself and many other women suffered at the hands of r. kelly. while many in the public are just learning about the extent of r. kelly's abuse and coming to grips with his chronic repulsive behavior, the abuse is something his victims have had to live and cope with for many years. because robert kelly was and is such a well-known powerful figure, there are individuals and entities who continue to try and protect him by attacking and blaming his victims. they attack us. these r. kelly enablers are engaged in a campaign to defame and slander my name and to re-victimize me, as well as others, in an effort to protect r. kelly and minimize his detestable and abhorrent behavior. i refuse to be a victim again. in december of last year, i took the first step towards standing up to these bullies and r. kelly accomplices by issuing the above cease and desist letters to several individuals through my attorneys. i hope that blogs and gossip sties will not continue to aid and abet the vicious harassment and bullying of these r. kelly accomplices, and instead will stand with myself and the other victims who deserve your support. his time is up. #muterkelly #metoo #asantemcgee#survivingrkelly

text:
iâ€™m going to try to be strong and watch the surviving r. kelly lifetime documentary tonight. i want to see first hand why the sudden outrage and hype. we have known for years about the accusations against r. kelly and his interest in young girls. now more comes out as many celebrities and others are outraged about the documentary.

why so much outrage now? where was all the outrage years ago when dave chappell and the boondocks were doing comedy skits about this? it wasnâ€™t funny then and it isnâ€™t funny now!

now there is also a muterkelly movement. this is a nationwide, grassroots movement to end the career of r&b singer and sexual abuser of young black women. i guess itâ€™s never too late to pay attention and listen but why does it have to take so much? i canâ€™t help but wonder, how many young girls and families could have been saved from this had more people took notice and paid attention earlier. this is the sad reality of the world we live in. 
this is why i do what i do, we have to start paying attention. we canâ€™t remain silent. so many are counting on us to speak up and so many more can find their voice, courage, and get help if we just listen and be supportive.

#sexyaftersexualassault #muterkelly #timesup #metoo #youarenotalone #enoughisenough #itcouldbeyourdaughter #ibelieveyou #nomorevictimblaming #alllivesmatter #bystanderintervention #supporteachother #payattention #nevergiveup #endviolenceagainstwomen  #lovenothateâ¤ï¸ #endrapeculture #listen

text:
i'm about to get personal now so if you're not interested, just hit like on the pretty images and just scroll on by. there is a deeper reason i take pictures beyond my love for "pretty" things. truth is i never felt pretty growing up. looking back, i can see now that i really was a cutie. i just didn't have the eyes i have today. 
this set of pictures (thanks to my baby girl for being my muse)  beautifully explains who i was then. "beautifully silenced" 
just a pretty little girl without a voice surrounded by obstacles that caged me in. the things that were happening to me at the hands of people i should have been able to trust stole my innocence & my life for many years. shame was hidden behind an unending quest to be perfect on the outside while i remained horribly sad inside. i became a cynical, opinionated, competitive, over-achiever with lots of relational conflict on a continual quest for something or someone to make me feel like i had a purpose. 
in school i was bullied because of what i looked like & as i matured i lashed back or ran away.i tried to be what the world wanted. they still didn't want me..and some still don't. 
today i realize that my story is just one of millions that  can say #metoo. we know darkness but can can learn to live in light. i'm proof. i know what it's like to not have 1 person get it. unless you have actually experienced sexual abuse, you truly don't know what it does to your mind. but please believe me when i say, you can live a normal life. you can heal. today i do know who i am. yes, it's work. everyday. good days or bad i know my struggles will pass. i once had a therapist tell me i was like a little bird with a broken wing and it would always be that way. she was so wrong. so much of me has been restored. when i hit my final bottom, & in my hopelessness i chose to look up. the creator of the universe i hadn't previously really knew i got to know and learned that he says i'm worthy. he says i'm loved. he said i'm his. the love of jesus changed my life for good. he has given me gifts. gifts like this i get to share with you all today.  #nevergiveup and thank you to those who choose to read.

text:
very true. 
from being raped at 14 and 16 i learned a lot from that time in my life. 
being diagnosed with crohn's at 18 on july 2, 2008 and almost dying in october 2009 from crohn's. 
that taught me more about myself. 
i was 80 lbs and in the hospital for 3 weeks. major surgery. away from my parents and my daughter. 
i didn't know if i would make it home to my baby girl.
hard things in life teach you things and you realize that down the road. 
you are strong, and you grow from every thing that happens. 
#strength #quotes #raped #crohns #lessonslearned #crohnsdisease #mother #life #metoo

text:
with all of the controversy that is going on with #survivingrkelly and all of us that have been through abuse by the hands of a man... i want to make sure to make this statement. 
dear black man, 
we love u. we will not let the actions of one man make us look at u any different. we appreciate u. we have your back. we know that us as queens need our kings to be a powerful force in this cruel world of hate. we will continue to fight by your side and unite our kingdoms. through this journey there will be sacrifices, there will be traders. there will be some whom don't believe in the love and respect that we have for one another. those people we must let go. r. kelly is one of those. he didn't respect us queens. he believes in only self and not unity. as hard as it is, we must sacrafice him and let him go. that is no way a reflection on u, black man. we love u. we respect u. we appreciate u and we cherish u. 
with love, 
black women

text:
issa bout time!!! #cyntoiabrown, a woman serving a life sentence for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16 years old, has been granted clemency, the #tennessee governor's office.
____________
the campaign for cyntoia brown's clemency brown will be released to parole supervision on august 7 after serving 15 years in prison, gov. #billhaslam's office said in a statement. "this decision comes after careful consideration of what is a tragic and complex case," haslam said.
___________
"cyntoia brown committed, by her own admission, a horrific crime at the age of 16. yet, imposing a life sentence on a juvenile that would require her to serve at least 51 years before even being eligible for parole consideration is too harsh, especially in light of the extraordinary steps ms. brown has taken to rebuild her life. transformation should be accompanied by hope."
___________
brown's case drew the attention of several high-profile advocates including a number of  celebrities like #amyschumer, #amandaseales, #kimkardashian,actress #ashleyjudd were among the many who called for brown's #clemency.

text:
here are some stats about sexual assault on college campuses. this convo is important to have but what about everything that goes on before college? high school, middle school? we have to address the different cultures and attitudes that have contributed to this issue from the very beginning. we canâ€™t limit this conversation to just higher education/college campuses. sexist dress codes are implemented since middle school, the phrase "boys will be boys" is used throughout elementary, middle school, and high school
~
in a given school year, an estimated 58% of 7th - 12th graders experience some form of sexual violence, especially sexual harassment. a 2011 study published by @aauwnational investigated sexual violence that occurs in middle/high school & found that in an academic year, 13% of girls reported that they had been inappropriately touched in an â€œunwelcome sexual way," in this same year, 4% reported being forced to perform a sexual act, & 1 in 20 girls who had been sexually harassed transferred to a different school in hopes of avoiding the torment. we have to protect our young students!
.
.
.
stat credits: @motherjonesmag @aauwnational 
#metoo #believesurvivors #twbwomensmarch #twbforsurvivors #womenswave #truthtopower

my soul is weeping with joy. i have been very emotional over this case for some time. the irony that this decision has been granted on the heels of the 6 episode r. kelly docuseries on lifetime called "surviving r. kelly". i have been apart of the #muterkelly movement for sometime. i knew r. kelly had an issue, but he is an absolute monster. nonconviction does not make an individual not guilty, nor does a conviction make you guilty. i'm still processing a lot of the stories shared in the docuseries. throughout viewing the story i often felt like these stories could easily be a cyntoia story. #protectblackgirls #protectchildren #menstandup #bringbackourgirls #blackgirlsmatter #metoo #timesup #cyntoiabrown

text:
[3/5] for years, when i would look at old photographs of myself i would be so confused as to why i wasnâ€™t smiling in any of them. now i know why. i was bullied throughout middle school and high school which made my inner turmoil grow even more, and as if things couldn't get worse i was date-raped at 15. being raped added a layer to the emotional damage that was already a fixture inside of my soul, but this time i felt i had to tell someone because the stakes were too high. i decided to open up to my mom about what had happened and even revealed that my uncle had molested me, i have made peace with the fact that my motherâ€™s response to my truth was less than ideal. as is common with many survivors of sexual abuse, the onus is always on us, the victims, to explain what we â€œdidâ€ to contribute to the assault taking place regardless of how old we are. as a result of the lack of validation, i internalized messages of self-blame and self-hatred. after that attempt, i never felt comfortable speaking about it again. the way i coped with my silence was by partying on weekends and using drugs, i kept the company of men who were destructive and hung out with the wrong crowd. my parents would try to get a hold of me when i was out but i refused to come home, i wanted to run away and i didnâ€™t want to live in my body anymore. popping ecstasy seemed so much easier than having to bear the burden of so much trauma, so i would use it to escape the realities of my life. one of the silver linings in my childhood was my relationship with my sister, ruchika (pictured here). the only photographs i have of myself in my early days where i am smiling are when i am with her. i went into mama bear mode at young age and i think itâ€™s because deep down i didnâ€™t want the same thing that had happened to me to happen to her. despite all the pain and the heartache that i experienced so young, there was a desire to protect and shelter others, which has pushed me to live to tell my story.

text:
r. kelly is reportedly creating a website to expose all of his accusers. 
the r. kelly story just keeps on getting more and more complicated. this weekend, twitter absolutely blew up after each episode of surviving r. kelly aired. the docu-series focuses on the years of abuse that the singer has been accused of handing out. in each episode, interviews with his accusers are shown and the artist is obviously not pleased with the outcome. many are calling for him to be blacklisted from the industry, claiming that enough is finally enough. others are waiting for kellz to explain himself. those of you that are putting a pause on cancelling him right away will be interested in learning that r. kelly is reportedly planning to go down his list of accusers one by one, exposing them all as liars. 
according to tmz, r. kelly will soon be going live with a website called survivinglies.com. as of now, a facebook page exists under the same name and it seems as though the singer will be going after asante mcgee first. the publication notes that r. kelly will go down his list of accusers one by one in an attempt to prove that they are all lying about him. 
people close to the artist are stating that he will soon be launching the website, which will reveal his accusersâ€™ â€œtrue motivations.â€ with dozens of women speaking out against the singer, he likely has his work cut out for him with this. what do you guys think? get the full details at www.itskenbarbie.com #rkelly #robertkelly #survivingrkelly #muterkelly #metoo #lifetime #lifetimetv #trappedinthecloset #entertainment #entertainmentnews #entertainmentblog #survivinglies

text:
when it comes to buying a home, i prefer the first option. buy something small, simple and cheap. it's better to pay for a place that has all utilities worked into the hoa. the hoa can go up or down depending on the board members greed.

most old people live in apartments until they reach the senior home, so avoid the massive house, think like you're 60. canadians buy cheap apartments and trailer homes in fla, so they retire much more than americans, cuz americans have huge mortgages.

if you want to buy with mortgage, buy something under 150k new or under 100k auction/foreclosed. hopefully you have a trade that can go anywhere so you can move where homes are cheap. if you're in ny or cali, you're screwed.

there are two type of people buying homes, dumb asses and wise asses.

when a dumb ass says i'm going to spend 500k on a home that means he'll search for a home within the 250k-500k and buy it.

when a wise person says i'm going to spend 500k on a home,  that means he will search for a home within 100-250k range and buy it cash.

with the remaining 250k he can setup a trust that pays all the bills automatically out of the remainder.

he can also do what smart ball players do (the ones you don't hear about). purchase the home 250k with your 500k budget in mind. put 100k into home repair account. pay 50k on taxes up front and another 50k on utilities/insurance upfront.

very few people do this option but this is how you buy with security and peace of mind. the same rule applies to a person buying a 50k studio. if your budget is 100k for a studio,  buy a foreclosure and have some friends in construction and remodeling do the fix up for about 25k.

with the remainder, put 15k on taxes and 10k on utilities/insurance. if your taxes are 1000 a year on a 50k studio. you paid 15 years up front assuming the price stays the same (which it won't). therefore if anything happens, whether you end up in a coma, injured, go to prison or whatever, you have a home with bills and taxes paid for next 20-30 years.

you can use the extra income to go back to school and get another trade to be able to make your own home remodels or save up for another cheap place you can rent out.

â£
iâ€™m also willing to be wrong. â£
â£
i help burnt-out women because i was a burnt-out woman. i was running on empty, hustling, working, giving so much to others and not replenishing my own cup. â£
â£
burn out looked like:â£
â£
severe fatigue where no amount of coffee could help. â£
crying before going into work because i had nothing in me.â£
painful periods that made me vomit.â£
a messy home because i would give and do so much for others i didnâ€™t even have the energy to support myself. â£
low sex drive.â£
bloating. â£
crippling anxiety.â£
depression where i couldnâ€™t see myself as worthy because everyone and everything else took precedent. â£
â£
in the thick of #timesup #metoo and more, itâ€™s imperative that women learn how to take care of themselves so we can continue to show up everyday and dismantle toxic masculinity. â£
â£
and it starts with you. â£
how you talk to yourself.â£
how you wake up in the morning.â£
how you move about your day. â£
â£
it starts in your kitchen.â£
your yoga class.â£
your bath. â£
â£
consider ayurveda as part of your tool bag. something you can return to over and over no matter how youâ€™re feeling. â£
â£
ayurveda is a life-long practice and iâ€™m in it for longevity, to avoid burn-out and to know how to navigate it if it does happen again. â£
â£
this wisdom is within me and itâ€™s within you, too. sometimes we just need someone to hold the mirror. â£
â£
send me a message if this speaks to you and we can work together to support you during and after burn-out. â£
â£
sending you all so much love. xo

text:
lemme tell yall sumthin, i'll do life behind mine. two words:jailhouse. one word: commissary. three words: the big house.. i'm raising a daughter very much unlike how i was raised, a free thinking, free speaking young lady who dont mind telling u how she feels n what's on her mind n heart. i grew up much different, "what goes on in this house, stays in this house,""nobody likes a tattletale, stop telling so much." if a grown mfa did sumthin to u, u turn the other way, "nobody will believe u anyways." no, tell me. ill believe u. ill give my whole heart for u. i'm teaching my daughter it's not #metoo its #notme. 
now, being a midwest girl, not far from chicago, we always heard those rumors(look at previous post, pic of him an aaliyah). always heard the stories of him lurking, oh but baby he wasnt the only one in the black community getting all the lil black girls cause nobody cared about us. mfs just chopped it up to "preference" or "them lil girls too mfn fast" n sum were, alot were not. u dont understand the power an older man can have over a young girls body n mind, unless you've been in those shoes. imma tell u this, its sumwhere i dont want my daughter to be, n she wont be.. let a mfn think they gon lock ms. mia up n keep her away from me n do wtf he please with her, my daughter has to ask to pee, eat, shower..u got me fucked up n ain't no standing outside throwing punk ass rocks at a window. bitch, this whole building coming down, imma run my car thru the door. dominique's mom, gets the mother of the century award, she went up in there n got her baby with nobody

text: â€œsurviving r kellyâ€ the docuseries was compelling on so many levels. i commend dream hampton on bringing together individuals - entertainment industry insiders, family, and victims. iâ€™m certain this was no easy task as many people donâ€™t chose to speak on this topic. i myself struggled in my decision on whether or not i should post about this for several reasons. i am among many who continued to mute my protest of r kellyâ€™s alleged behavior by purchasing his music and listening to it on the radio and at events. also this a touchy, personal conversation for many of us. so the decision to address this on a public platform came after a bit of internal deliberation and conversations with several friends. the docuseries clearly states at its start that r kelly was once a victim himself. for that, i feel sad for the little boy who never got help for the abuse and neglect he suffered at the hands of family and other adults in his life. but this does not negate his poor choices to not deal with his own issues, rather turn the abuse on innocent people. to hear the depth of of r kellyâ€™s warped ideas of relationships, his misuse of his platform, and his total abuse of power through his gift and blessings is sickening. i am not the judge nor jury of his career or ultimate fate in life. i do truly hope that through this spotlight, through the pain that we hear from victims, that the injustice that r kelly has been allowed to commit, i pray it all comes to an end. we have to hold ourselves accountable for how we exalt individuals because of their talents, money, or power. wrong is wrong. letâ€™s not ignore what is right before our eyes. #muterkelly

text:
four years after graduating college... .
â€¢
i was reporting live in front of the white house for nbc. if i looked scared shitless, i was. .
â€¢
this was the biggest moment in my young tv journalist career to date. .
â€¢
i had just turned 25. it was the white house. my dress was from marshallâ€™s. i may have overdrafted to even buy it. .
â€¢
if i looked scared shitless, i was for another reason too. .
â€¢
moments before this picture was taken, a man of great power and authority cornered me in the hallway outside the room i was about to go live in. 
he brushed up against my leg. i could smell his stale breath against my cheek as he called me â€œdollâ€ and offered to â€œhelpâ€ me. .
â€¢
it would be the first of countless times i was sexually harassed in this industry. .
â€¢
i tell you the former because never be surprised at how quickly your dreams and goals manifest when youâ€™re clear and work damn hard. .
â€¢
i share with you the later to never lose hope that, as bob dylan says, the times. they are a changing. .
â€¢
share this with any young woman so she sees weâ€™ve been fighting to make sure she never even *knew there was a glass ceiling. .
â€¢

take a moment to read my thoughts: i boycotted r. kelleys music in 2002 when i saw the video ~ i know it was him. clearly.  i wasnâ€™t comfortable talking about it because the world i lived in .... everyone thought it was a joke, and they made me feel ike i was too earnest. i saw the bbc documentary, i read the buzz feed and new yorker articles ... as a #survivor and a black woman in the music industry, i just broke down sobbing when i saw the video. i sobbed, because it was a graphic illustration, that i lived in a world that didnt value people like me. and i had to learn to take care of myself in the face of a society and industry that doesnâ€™t love me. i learned that i had to wear the crown of my ancestors and hold my own head up. and its been hard. but i do it because i believe in my mission ~ i donâ€™t need to sing about the fight , my mission is to administer to the people in the fight. humanity makes me sad all the time ~ the things were going thru ... but also today, iâ€™m hopeful, that we as a group are now #muterkelly ~ but, i wont be satisfied until every #survivor know, that â€œeveryone of us is worthyâ€ and when ever someone treats us as less, that is thier mistake, ... and while the wound is not our doing, it is our responsibility ~ we have to heal ourselves.  that healing can take on so much more momentum, when the world around us is healing too.... so i feel good today knowing that we as a collective are waking up even more, to the ways that the world / the music industry / the society / the culture ~ harm our women and girls.  and! i feel good today knowing that these growing pains are about growth. we are all! worthy and significant and we matter! because we exist!  may we keep waking up to that fact. it is a fact! everyone of us is #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #survivingrkelly #iamlight #muterkelly #survivingrkelly #rkelly #blackgirlsmatter #metoo

text:
this is the year that i launch my non-profit i am still looking for board members who are really dedicated to the cause of helping black and brown girls and women who are victims of sexual abuse and trafficking in inner city neighborhoods... my mission is focused on rescue and reintroduction/rehabilitation into a stable life. by now many of you have seen surviving r. kelly and know the impact it can have not only on the victims but their families. i know we all have been, or know someone who has fallen victim to predatory behavior... especially in our own community. i've been working toward this for about the last 2 years and starting to round things out. even if you're not interested... i'm asking that you share my post so that it gets into the hands of someone truly dedicated to helping this cause.

#survivingrkelly #turningvictimstosurvivors #sextrafficking #sextraffickingawareness #sexualviolence #sexualabuse #innercities #philly #chicago #detroit #atlanta #miami #newyork #brownwomen #blackwomen #blackgirlmagic #metoo #muterkelly

text:
hey klubbers! this weekend i took the time out to watch the 6 part documentary on surviving r.kelly! as i watched with the million of viewers i watched not subconsciously knowing the history and constant quiet reminders of jokes made through black culture.(boondocks episode). â€¢ 
as me and my friends watch this together we discussed very different but understanding view points on the subject. we acknowledge the abuse and victimization, the long history of sexual misconduct with minors that weâ€™ve ignored as a collective. we talked about separating the monster from the music (if thatâ€™s possible and do we have to chose). it made a face our own traumatic experiences with older guys weâ€™ve encountered during this life journey. if you can watch it. black women deserve to be believed, support and nurtured too! â€¢ 
hug on your daughter,
mother, sister, cousin and more. we are changing the narrative around the treatment of black women, motherhood, business and community now letâ€™s continue the fight but without forgetting the victimization and molestation of our brown boys either. there are causes we can stop. â€¢
#blackmomsbelike #survivingrkelly #sexual #metoo #blackwomen #community #philadelphia #blackmotherhood #saveourbabies #conversationstarters

text:
stop the silence!! after an amazing weekend with fellow men of achievement in tampa florida for kappa alpha psi fraternity,  inc. 14th annual founders day.  i found myself up late sunday evening watching hours of "surviving r. kelly" on lifetime.  words cannot begin 2 describe my disappointment in us as a society for decades of abuse, sexual assault,  manipulation,  and degradation of young teenage girls. â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†
how and why has this illegal activity been allowed 2 go on for so long?  the moral compass of our country is really at an all time low.  the docuseries featured survivors of r. kelly's cult, former staff, friends and family of the victims.  i applaud their bravery for speaking out and not remaining silent.  thank you 2 tom joyner, chance the rapper, and john legend for taking a conscious stand against r. kelly.  we need more men in this movement 2 truly move the needle in the right direction.  especially since most of the perpetrators of rape and sexual assault are males.  as a gender we as males are a big part of the problem.  and now it's time 2 be a bigger part of the solution. â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†
everyone has a voice and should use it for the betterment of us all. "silence is the antithesis of effectiveness." dont just sit idly by and allow this history of violence 2 continue.  2 many people have been adversely affected and so many suffer in silence. future generations need you 2 shield them from abuse. hidden and unspoken cycles of sexual violence is a problem. which is why i've served as an advocate for over 2 decades. hopefully you will use your platform and stand with me. ğŸ’«

text:
survivors of violence (interpersonal, systemic) i believe you, i see you. your story is valid, your life is beautiful.
.
.
femmes and non binary folks of color- your bodies & lives are beautiful, may those who hurt you fall, may they repent.
.
all oppressed beings- what binds us is our struggle for recognition & healing. i believe in our abilities to thrive.
.
in the past iâ€™ve opened up donation based protection spells for survivors. i donâ€™t really have the spoons for that at the moment... but iâ€™ll let yâ€™all know when i open up the spots again.
.
.
in the meantime- remember to take care of your heart. use lots of rosemary. put her fragrance on himalayan sea salt & throw it in the bath. warm your skin with her scent. hang her above your doorways. plant some marigolds, or poach some from a rich persons yard. dry them. put them in a bowl with lavender. carry rose quartz with you in your bag or pocket. burn cedar, bay leaves, douglas fir tips, mugwort or angelica root. write yourself a love letter.
.

i'm not going to blame the youth. i shan't blame this on them, as we all know what it's like to be young, still having much to learn, but i do have a #straythought as all of these incidents pop up:

fvck age of consent laws because many states do have them too young, but in a culture where we celebrate a woman's maturity at ages such as 15 and 16 i.e. quinceaneras and sweet 16s, i find it interesting how we celebrate these parties from a lens of "coming into adulthood" yet are dumbfounded and consequently revoke titles of maturation if/when scenarios like this come up.

17 is still technically illegal in the eyes of federal law so drake fucked up, especially including the statements he made, but just the idea of why we still hold these big coming-of-age parties, calling them such and not simply just birthdays, yet revoke such adulthood in multiple instances is ironic in my eyes.

it seems we as a society groom children and teens in various ways for that treatment but then grown ass people take it upon themselves to take advantage of such and we are baffled ?????? it's our fault (society i.e. media outlets, influencers, loved ones, etc.) and the fault of the predator but i think, above all the former is most reprehensible because we skew lines, telling our youth they're grown in many ways (vs growing) and then snatch their autonomy and re-emphasize the young in "young adult" when it no longer suits our conveniences. i don't think i have to explain as much as y'all can just reflect on your own upbringings and digest this thought.

all-in-all, we too often place this burden upon the youth of america and question why such cases as these exist (and frequently more) whilst complacently / complicitly ignoring that we are the culprits of these behaviors whether it be due to our nonchalance over these behaviors, our silence, or even a misdirection of blame.

everybody treats accountability like it's this nasty, accusatory word - but it's not. it's the one thing that could set us free if we were only strong enough to lay down our egos and change some sh*t.

drop thoughts below.
let's talk.

text: no the face i want starting my week not the post i would like to make on a monday but it is part of my mission to share the dark side of being human, of being empath,  a healer and ptsd from a narcissist relationship â€¢ this. morning i woke up feeling happy and ready to tackle the day, got my girls ready for school, both made it on time and both were ready to have a great day. after dropping valerie i stopped to do some grocery shopping, while doing that i started feeling off, watching over my back, anxious to get out and wanting to cry. once i got to my car i realized the ptsd from that trauma was kicking in, i felt frustrated, tired of if, weak.  i cried. in an attempt to clear my head i grab my phone and star seeing his name on a person comment, then i look around and i see a car same brand as his, i checked myself to make sure this all was mine and not that i was picking up from someone else, also to make@sure no creepy energy was trying to sneak on me. you see even seeing that can trigger you, thats how intense the abuse was. i donâ€™t like to see his, name, or anything related to reiki or his car brand. it triggers thoughts and then brings me back to all i went through, then i start asking myself how i let that happen. a full cycle until i am bring myself back and reach out to my support team. ptsd takes time to heal, the triggers show me how much healing i still need, how also how fast i bring myself back to the light when i have an â€œepisodeâ€. â€¢ all this because last night before going to bed i accidentally ended up reading someone else experience with a narc. â€¢ this shit is hard, but i also know this life lesson helps me heal and understand others better. give them tools based kn my own healing. fighting this battle help me guide other through theirs. â€¢ and for you asshole! i know you will read this, war is not over. i am a warrior of god....remember that.

text:
via @masslive: y.a.â€™s boyfriend called her names, pulled her hair, and punched her. he took her bank card and only let her use it in his presence, then emptied her bank account, so y.a. couldnâ€™t pay rent. finally, after the man choked y.a. to prevent her from leaving the house, she broke up with him.

y.a. told her landlord at the boston housing authority about the abuse and asked for time to make her payments. but y.a. had by that time negotiated multiple payment plans with the housing authority. the housing authority moved to evict her, and a housing court judge ruled that the authority could go ahead.

the federal violence against women act protects domestic violence victims from eviction, if their inability to pay rent is due to the abuse. the supreme judicial court will hear arguments on monday in the case boston housing authority vs. y.a. about the extent to which these protections apply, and how the federal protections interact with state law.

the court will decide whether y.a., who has two children, can stay in her home. the case could also clarify how public housing landlords and housing courts must treat domestic violence victims who struggle to pay rent. â€œfor victims trying to leave a domestic violence situation, the ability to have safe housing is critical,â€ said jamie sabino, an attorney with the massachusetts law reform institute who filed an amicus brief with other domestic violence advocates in support of y.a. â€œwere she not to be able to stay in her apartment â€¦ and have to try to find a home for herself and her children, there might be a possibility of having to go back to the abuser at some point.â€ full article: https://www.masslive.com/news/2019/01/does-domestic-violence-protect-a-tenant-from-eviction.html

text:
last nightâ€™s golden globes ended not with a bang but with a whimper. or, at least, a baffling decision. bohemian rhapsody, the weakest of the five nominees in the best motion picture â€“ drama category, defied the bookiesâ€™ odds and won the biggest award of the evening.

though it was a box-office smash, the film, which stars rami malek as queen frontman freddie mercury, has been accused of mishandling the late singerâ€™s sexuality. a review in forbes magazine accused it of â€œrefram[ing] his life story as an afterschool special about the dangers of partying and gay sex ... whether itâ€™s homophobic or old-school slut-shaming, itâ€™s ickyâ€. the decision to hire director bryan singer, who has faced numerous sexual assault accusations dating back to the nineties (allegations he denies), also caused consternation.

on quality alone, the film didnâ€™t deserve to beat four such powerful, confidently realised creations as black panther, blackkklansman, if beale street could talk and a star is born. but given the more troubling context around it, bohemian rhapsodyâ€˜s win felt even more jarring â€“ particularly on a night that celebrated change and progress in the wake of the solemn mood that (rightly) defined last yearâ€™s proceedings.

text:
2018 marked the one-year anniversary of the #metoo movement, and while uk businesses, charities and politics continue to be hit by scandal and allegations of misconduct, the latter part of 2018 has seen a shift from outrage to action.
nonetheless, while the #metoo movement has been empowering, there are rumblings that it may also be a poison chalice. bloomberg reported a particularly worrying response of wall street firms to the movement whereby male colleagues are now reluctant to dine or travel with their female counterparts, while others prefer not to put themselves in one-on-one situations with female colleagues such as meetings, reviews or mentoring. in light of this, would it be too extreme to suggest that men may be more reluctant to hire women?
 so how do we tackle these attitudes? how do we ensure the issue of workplace harassment is taken seriously and addressed effectively without having a negative impact on diversity?
the key here is to involve men in the conversation. female only panel discussions attended by female only audiences are not environments for change. indeed, a comsres survey in 2017 found that 18% of men had experienced unwanted sexual behaviour in the workplace so this isnâ€™t exclusively a â€œwomanâ€™s issueâ€.
we need to avoid further polarising gender issues and discuss the challenges collectively â€“ as iâ€™ve said before, men are allies, not enemies.

text:
ladies imagine this:

we stop idealizing marriage and start acting like a (insert age) year old with her whole life ahead of her.  you go to that dream school, you get an education, you travel the world, you write that book,  you start a business and you stop assuming your life starts and ends witb a husband. .
.
.
i chose this picture because i once drank the koolaid.  i once thought my only puropse was to nurture those around me.  i married young and poured myself into his dreams and the dreams of being married and raising beautiful, self assured children.  i left myself and my dreams on the back burner so much that it took  years to figure out which dreams were my own.
.
.
.
this is a picture of a trip i paid for.  that i took my children on.  a hike deep in the  jungle that i wanted to take.  where we found a waterfall (a huge passion of mine) that i wanted to swim in.  i got out of my own way during this trip.  i set my own fears aside.  i nurtured my dreams (and my children too)!! turns out both can happen at once!! ladies please love yourselves.  you are an entity worthy of love and compassion and you deserve to be a priority!!!
#loribrinkleycounseling #mentalwellness #boundaries #selfloverevolution #metoo

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
showing no sign of abating, the #metoo movement continued to traverse the globe in full force. morphing under new names from #anakaman in egypt to #sendearlat in turkey, #beknownbeheard in nigeria. 
the conversation on sexual abuse grew and the can of worms began to open on sexual offenders across the world, unseating powerful men in it's path from politics to entertainment. 
the pressure increased on the government and companies alike to change their polices on violence against women. 
#metoo in u.s. alone cost more than 200 prominent men their jobs. the u.s. equal employment opportunity commission recovered nearly usd 70 million on behalf of sexual harassment survivors in 2018 fiscal year. 
sadly africa, (nigeria especially) is far behind in the fight against gender-based violence and other offenses of sexual nature.. at truss we have highlighted a numbers of activities for 2019 which includes partnerships to continually join forces with other organizations at the fore front of this fight with the aim of propelling nigeria towards the sdgs and getting a 50/50  world where men and women have equal opportunities by #2030

we are excited about all the work we are set to do to empower women across board.. we can't wait to tell all women #workitmama .
.
.
#trussempowermentfoundation
#beknownbeheard

text:
there are so many hurting people out here hurting other people. 
it's not any one person's fault, but it does require that we each acknowledge and accept what is being shared/expressed.

#muterkelly and #metoo go hand in hand with #saysomething and #tellsomebody.

parents, please listen to your children and watch for physical queues. if you don't speak up and protect them,  you leave them to hurt all through life and wait for that pain to manifest in other,seemingly odd, ways or times.

victims and survivors, please be alright with growing through your trauma. don't allow anyone to diminish your experiences just so they can feel like they're helping you. be strong in acknowledging and accepting that you were wronged and victimized by someone.

stop trying to make healing and forgiveness happen overnight. yes...you are better than you were yesterday. but,  all the things you had to face, feel and fight through as a victim are what made/ makes/ will make you victorious.

text:
here is an article about dry january and how it's not so bad but i thought this was the most interesting line.... it's so challenging to be sober even for someone without a drinking problem that he lies about it because it is that bad to deal with the comments this decision comes with. 
this man doesn't want to deal with the judgemental looks and mean comments so he just lies but i refuse to lie about consuming alcohol. why should i have to? why is soberity so scandalous?

when i first got sober one of my "friends" told me to lie about this, no man would ever date me if i had a drinking problem.  it's so sad that this is somewhat true and that we are in a society where sobriety is so shocking is must be kept secret. 
there are 15 million people who are struggling with alcohol addiction and as a society we have been so rude and mean about sobriety that these people feel it's best to lie about it, there is no way they will be accepted as they are. to think my friends are dying from alcohol abuse and they can't tell anyone, what other illness is treated without any compassion and must be lied about? why? why do we treat alcoholic people so badly? we glamorize the recovery of celebrities like rob lowe but not our friends and family members. 
let's end the stigma attached to sobriety 
let's stop lying about how wonderful alcohol is and be more accepting of someone's decision to say no thanks 
#drydiet #sober #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #transformation #soberissexy #soberyogi #transformation #liveyourtruth #soberaf #recovery #recoveroutloud

text:
unadulterated yet wild. bear with me, for i have felt this free for the first time in what felt like a forever. i want to hold on to this feeling, this happiness. there's no man in my life, and i haven't felt this free ever. there is no man in my life, that i need to hold on to so he won't leave. there's no man in my life, so all the definitions of "me", "proper" and "future" are mine. i've been on life support for a long time. i need to feel this. i will remain present. i will let this sadness consume me. i will not push myself from another cliff for a man to validate me. i will not. i cannot. leave me or love me, i cannot be a part of this cycle anymore. and i will not.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
i don't believe that every abusive person is capable of murder.  i know not every survivor has a fear of being murdered...but some of us do and that fear is a tough one to shake.  when we went to mediation last year, the mediator came into the room with my attorney and me and told me kyles response to a basic question was one he had never heard before.  it was quite alarming. he then asked me what joint custody meant to me, i said "we both have a say on major life decisions; school, religion, medical" which is the obvious answer. 
kyles response "i get them when something happens to her" 
what????? first i'm not planning on going anywhere and for that to be his only reason for wanting joint custody only added to my fear of him eventually murdering me.  we have court a week from today and i know it's not going to be a good day for him. he spent the $4000 in child support and hasn't seen the boys since april.  i tried to tell the judge so many times he was only doing all of this to get back at me, he told me that, but she said i couldn't say that because he's stating he loves the boys and truly wants a relationship with them.  now, everything i said is going to be clear as day to her; his games will be seen and a narcissist never likes that.  i'm praying hard this week for safety, peace, and to keep my heart kind. 
i won't be a dateline story
(he didn't get joint custody or any set visitation)

.

text:
for far too long black women were seen as less than human in the sense we are expected to endure so much without breaking, we are to accept the hand weâ€™re dealt without question. studies have shown that even in the medical profession black women are believed to be able to endure more pain and are dismissed when they come with concerns. as a result black girls are dismissed, are often taught to suppress their emotions further damaging (intentional or not) their feelings of self worth and confidence. itâ€™s time we stop silencing our girls. their pain is real whether you agree or not. it deserves validation. give them a voice and be a part of the solution.

text:
under the control of her abuser
when he call she comes running!
he black her eye she ask why?Â 
he beats her senseless
she looks at him in bewilderment!
surprised every time!
she tries and she tries to be what he desires
never quite reaching the markÂ 
never quite being good enough
his rejection leaves her starving for his affection
trading her dignity for his acceptance!
more submissive less attractive, more agreeable less vocal, more domesticated less social, more teachable less successful!Â 
every time she reaches the line he moves it!Â 
forever chasing his delusions... just like an abused woman! 
mind control...history repeats
we keep doing the same ol' thing
and excepting something different.
insanity...
conforming to a world you weren't created to be a part of
fighting to be a part of a system perverse and corrupt
pleading, begging, marching, protesting
picket lines, picket signs
singing, screaming... #nojusticenopeace equality
generation after generation, decade after decade, year after year for hundreds of years
day after day we kneel in rejection 
beggin
cries fall on deaf earsÂ 
if it ain't broke why fix it?
there ain't no problem if i don't see it
justice is blind! 
but we keep on tryin'
we knockin'
we dyin'
we hopin' that one day 
we'll be seen as more than three fifths of a human being! *the abuser never thinks he's abusive! *freedom's on the other side... open the door walk through it!
come up hear and see!
if we change the way we think, we'll change what we've been seeing!Â 
wake up
#repentorperish
Â scream shout yell it out!
#4cryinoutloud911.com

i'm not sure how many have watched the disturbing #survivingrkelly series on @lifetimetv but i watched the first 2 parts of it with my daughter. i must say, i'm all over the place with my feelings on this subject. i have so many questions. questions for the people around r. kelly, questions for the girls, questions for his family, but mainly questions for the parents who allow their minor children to hang out with and befriend adults nearly twice their age ğŸ˜¡ğŸ˜¤. i don't want to hear about parents not always knowing what their children are doing. there was a pattern and these girls were with him all of the time. call me a helicopter mom, but i know who my children are with, the parents names, their addresses, how many additional adults live in the household, ect. you're not going to tell me that a 20 something year old man has 15 year old female friends. nope, nope, nope. not buying it ğŸ™…ğŸ¾â€â™€ï¸! we all as a society have failed these girls. everyone that watched his sex tape that was released early 2002, is responsible for what happened to all those girls that followed. why didn't anyone speak up? his team, the record executives, his teachers, the parents of these girls? why are we still justifying sexual abuse by saying things like, "well why did they wait so long to talk?", or, "if it really happened he would be in jail". this way of thinking is why so many do not speak up. stop saying things like that to people! stop saying things like that out loud! i'm sure i'll have more to say on this topic in the coming days after i watch the final parts to this. if you watch it, i suggest breaking it up, it's too much to take in all in one sitting. if you've watched it, i'd love to hear your thoughts. .

text:
wooden wrinkles
~
layers of seconds leading minutes into years, thickening until nothing else may be seen or felt.
~
layers-upon-layers folding over the seed and losing it forever.
~~
layers tucking the vulnerable in by swallowing them whole, thickening until nothing else may be seen or felt.
~
layers of wooden wrinkles...the only of the me out in a lonely world.

text:
thank you speaker of the house nancy pelosi reception. san francisco, california 01.06.2019

congratulations speaker of the house nancy pelosi, icon of female power, reclaims role as speaker and seal place in history.

if you believe nothing else, please know you are worthy of unconditional love and acceptance - just as you are. â¤

pelosi statement on one year anniversary of supreme court ruling on marriage equality.

washington, d.c. â€“ house democratic leader nancy pelosi today released this statement on the anniversary of the supreme court decision on marriage equality, which was announced on june 26, 2015: â€œthis weekend, we mark one year since the supreme court unequivocally affirmed that equal justice means marriage equality.  in communities across america, loving lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender americans are finally free to marry who they love and enjoy the same rights and privileges as other married couples.  with this monumental decision, america moved closer to fulfilling the promise of our greatest ideals. â€œone year later, however, lgbt americans are still targets of violence and a shameful agenda of discrimination advancing in statehouses and in the congress.  nearly two weeks after the heartbreaking anti-lgbt mass shooting that claimed the lives of 49 people and terrorized the lgbt community, congress must unite to disarm hate.  we must strive to end anti-lgbt discrimination everywhere by passing the equality act. â€œwe rejoice at how far we have come together.  thanks to president obama, the stonewall inn is now a national monument.  in toppling â€˜donâ€™t ask, donâ€™t tellâ€™, passing inclusive hate crimes legislation, and winning marriage equality, we have the forward momentum needed to usher in a new era of progress for america.  let us continue to ensure equality for lgbt families, reject discrimination, and act to improve our country for all.â€ #madamspeaker #speakerpelosi #forthepeople #imwithher #nancypelosi

text:
#motivationalmonday

not too long ago my health was fading pretty fast... my life consisted of constant doctor visits and hospitals stays... on a good day i would take 19 pills ... on a bad day, i wouldn't be able to honestly tell you. it was pretty bad. i took what doctors told me and ran with it. every label they slapped on me, i wore. seemed like every lab work done came back with something new. pill after pill... treatment after treatment... and still i wasn't getting any better. i would spend my days in bed (tossing and turning because i wasn't able to sleep) and my nights throwing up medications non stop... got so bad that i named my toilet "booskie" ... i mean we spent all night cuddling, might as well name it. 
shit got pretty bad... my anxiety was off the charts... popping xanax on top of all my medications just so i could get some rest... which only made me irritable because sleep was something my body forgot how to do. i was hospitalized, had morphine pumping through my veins... and still no sleep. my body didn't know what to do with itself... i went 4 days of no sleep... by that 4th day ending it all was all i could think of. not because i hated life... but because i was tired of being tired.

then one day it happened...you can say i got mad... i cold turkey stopped all meds and treatments... i googled foods, vitamins, oils, and herbs i could use as an alternative. my primary of over a decade did not agree with my decision, and mailed me a letter letting me know they could no longer be my health care provider as i was going against their recommendations. i think getting that letter was the push i needed to take control of my life... i did just that... went to my local police station and dropped off all pills... i was doing this! ... the withdrawal stage was hell, to say the least... my body still feels the effects of all those pills.... especially my kidney and stomach. my journey has not been easy... and far from over... still dealing with health issues but i got this. there's no stopping me now... i've been enlightened!ğŸ’œ

text:
we are excited to celebrate this yearâ€™s first #featuredrosie @lynzylab ! thank you for sharing your #rosiestory with us!
.
.
it was the day after kavanaugh was sworn in, and i was sitting at home alone when i noticed my husband had forgotten to lock the door when he left for work that morning. i immediately got up to lock it, thinking to myself, â€œwow! anyone could have just walked in and tried to hurt me.â€ i didnâ€™t agonize over the thought; it was just an impulse i had, and have had, many times before in similar situations. i was reminded of trumpâ€™s words about it being a scary time for the men in this country, and i chuckled at the irony. but that laughter soon turned to anger, and i began writing a song that, unbeknownst to me, would drastically change the course of my life.
.
i had no idea a scary time (for boys) would go viral when i posted it on social media that evening, but in three daysâ€™ time, the video racked up over 60 million views worldwide. the fact that it resonated with so many people in such a short time is a true testament to how many others felt exactly how i had been feeling in the wake of the ford-kavanaugh hearing, and long before that. of course, i have also received a ton of negative criticism from people who disagree with the songâ€™s message, or who incorrectly assume iâ€™m saying all men are bad. many also argue that women can do most of the things mentioned in the song, which is true. i do those things. but not without checking my surroundings. not without hearing my dadâ€™s voice in my head, telling me to yell as loudly as i can if someone tries to rape me. not without holding my keys between my fingers to use as a weapon.
.
the bottom line is: if my husband had been home alone and noticed the door wasnâ€™t locked, he would have locked it (maybe), and that would have been that. when i noticed, my first instinct was to lock it as soon as possible, and then feel instant relief that nothing terrible happened to me in the hours that it was unlocked. thatâ€™s what the song is about.
.

i had no idea a scary time (for boys) would go viral when i posted it on social media that evening, but in three daysâ€™ time, the video racked up over 60 million views worldwide. the fact that it resonated with so many people in such a short time is a true testament to how many others felt exactly how i had been feeling in the wake of the ford-kavanaugh hearing, and long before that. of course, i have also received a ton of negative criticism from people who disagree with the songâ€™s message, or who incorrectly assume iâ€™m saying all men are bad. many also argue that women can do most of the things mentioned in the song, which is true. i do those things. but not without checking my surroundings. not without hearing my dadâ€™s voice in my head, telling me to yell as loudly as i can if someone tries to rape me. not without holding my keys between my fingers to use as a weapon.

text:
popped out to #ateasesundays open mic in #chicago last night. this poem is called complicit to agreement. we have a dangerous culture of sexual abuse, sexual misconduct, and sexual inappropriateness. and social media has helped us to better identify who some of you really are. i'm thankful for the men and women who have been courageous enough to speak their truth. i'm thankful for the men and women who have chosen not to deflect, but rather try to understand. i'm thankful for the men and women who have publicly and privately identified themselves as part of the problem and are actively doing something about it. and lastly, i'm so thankful for the advocates and treatment teams that are available to support survivors in this retraumaitizing societal echo chamber of blame and shame. the sexual abuse hotline calls surged this weekend for a reason. please reach out to 1-800-656-hope (4673) if you need to talk with someone or receive local resources. further, if you know of or suspect that an adult is having a sexual relationship with a minor, please contact your local authorities and the national child abuse hotline at 1-800-25-abuse. even if the sexual contact happened in the past, please report it. reports can be made anonymously. 
thank you @jeronimo_speaks for capturing the moment.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.
